For more on this, let's speak now to author Mbali Mavundla. JOHANNESBURG - It's important to have motorists that are skilled and knowledgeable and less likely to contribute to accidents on the roads that's the aim of Author Mbali Mavundla's new book for children, 'Kids on the Roads.' The book gives young readers basic knowledge of the rules of the road, road signs, and the different career paths in the automotive industry. It's for pupils in Grade R to 7 but it can even be used for high schoolers.